%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G3.1: 3WHS negotiation, client AccECN-capable
(tcpEcnMode="accecn") but the server only understands classic ECN
(tcpEcnMode="rfc3168"). The client's SEWA SYN (ECE=CWR=AE=1) does NOT match
the server's classic-ECN-willing check (G3.2 requires AE=0 for that check
to fire -- draft-ietf-tcpm-accurate-ecn's resolution of an RFC 3168
ambiguity), so the server treats it as a plain non-ECN SYN and replies with
an unconditional classic ECN-setup SYN-ACK (ECE=1, CWR=0, AE=0) -- the
server's own ecnWillingness=true, unconditionally on any SYN, per its
pre-AccECN behavior. The client's G3.1 decode logic matches (1,0,0) and
falls back to classic ECN (ect=true, accEcnNegotiated stays false).

Real two-INET-instance handshake (see tcp_accecn_negotiate_accepted_1.test
for why this isn't hand-injected).

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script=""

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.cli_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"
*.srv_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "rfc3168"

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's SYN: SEWA -- unchanged, the client doesn't know yet that the server is classic-only.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.001 A001] A.1000 > B.2000: S E W N 0:0(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's SYN-ACK: SE. (classic ECN-setup, no AE) -- the server never recognized the SYN as AccECN.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.003 B001] A.1000 < B.2000: A S E 500:500(0) ack 1 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
AccECN request received classic-ECN SYN-ACK... falling back to RFC 3168 ECN.
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%not-contains: stdout
AccECN-setup SYN received
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
